Lucky Ntimane from the National Liquor Traders Council reacts to the President's address #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa says the sale of alcohol for both off-site and on-site consumption is prohibited for 14 days. Ramaphosa made the announcement on Sunday. He says this is to ease pressure on hospitals. READ: SA Lockdown: South Africa moves to alert level 4 The president also said there will be a nationwide curfew from 9pm to 4am. South Africa moves to adjusted alert level 4 of the lockdown from Monday morning.